Yum! I love the blueberry bran muffins at Whole Foods so was looking for a similar recipe. This is pretty close. I substituted frozen blueberries for the figs (added at the end), 1/2 cup milk mixed with 2 1/2 cup full fat yogurt as I didn't have buttermilk, and used salted butter instead of unsalted because that was all I had, and they were delicious. I used the recipe once before only substituting the blueberries, and it was good but not quite as good as with these 3 substutitions. (They were denser last time)

