Rating: 4
These turned out perfectly light, fluffy and moist. I used 1 1/4 cups spelt flour and 1 1/4 cups of whole wheat flour instead of all purpose. I used 1 cup of oat bran and 1 cup of wheat bran and added a 1/2 cup of ground flax seed. I used 1/2 cup of unsweetened applesauce in place of the butter. Instead of white sugar I used dark brown sugar. I added 1 tsp of apple pie spice and 1 tsp of pure vanilla. Used raisins instead of figs (hubby doesn't like figs). I think next time I will give maple syrup or agave nectar a try in place of honey and perhaps some citrus rind.

