I tried to healthify these: -1c whole wheat flour for part of the white flour -only used 1/2c white sugar -1c natural applesauce + 2T canola oil (for the butter) -2T white vinegar + enough skim milk to toal 2c for the buttermilk -used rasins and dried cranberries for the figs (just didn't have the figs) -drizzled a tiny bit of honey over each muffin prior to baking Results: They taste like good, healthy, bran muffins. I'll add more dried fruit next time and also try spraying the tins and not using the paper liners (lots of muffin lost stuck to the liner when cooked, boo!)

