Rating: 4
This is a great basic recipe for bran muffins-- the muffins, light, fluffy and delicious. It is also very versatile. Any dried fruit can be substituted for the figs, and adding nuts works nicely. I always keep a stock of these muffins in the freezer, and defrost in the microwave for breakfast.

Rating: 4
I came to this site looking for a good, easy bran muffin recipe, and this is it! I did make one fun substitution; I used huckleberries in place of the figs, and they were delicious. If you are cooking with frozen huckleberries (or most any other frozen berry), thaw them in warm water and drain them well before adding them to the batter as your final ingredient. Thawing prevents the berries from going soggy as they cook. Enjoy!

